{"key":"post-7410431","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7410431</id>\n<content>The  best way to break up a grain jar is to beat the hell out of it against a fully inflated tire.  I use a bicycle tire and air it up nice and hard before use.  Half a dozen bangs usually separates every kernel from every other kernel.  If not, it's a good sign your jar was contaminated with bacteria, which makes the kernels stick together like rubber.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7410588</next>\n<prev>7409631</prev>\n<first>6343358</first>\n<last>27872587</last>\n<when>1189815213</when>\n<utime>09/15/07 03:13 AM</utime>\n</post>"}